726410f-b.title: Queens: Corona Avenue - 90th Street
726410f-b.text:
Corona Avenue, north side, east of 90th Street, showing
St. Barks African M.E. Church and Cemetery. The African Church
as it was originally known was established in 1828 on donated
Droperty. It was repaired in 1925. The bodies lying in the
cemetery surrounding the chrch were removed therefrom to Mount
Olivet Cemetery about 1930. Now a series of two story buildings
stand in the former cemetery grounds.
Fen. 1924.
Views 1 \& 2
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
MAY BE REPRODUCED
